@{
    Layout = null;
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>@ViewData["Title"] - TrackIT</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/privacy.css" />
</head>
<body>

    <div class="privacy-container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> October 2025</p>

        <p>
            At <span class="highlight">C.A.T.S. (Container Asset Tracking Services)</span>, we respect your privacy and are committed
            to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard information
            through the <span class="highlight">TrackIT</span> platform, in accordance with the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA) of South Africa.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect and process only the data required to provide a secure and functional tracking service, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal details</strong> — name, email, contact number, and company affiliation.</li>
            <li><strong>Tracking data</strong> — container IDs, GPS coordinates, timestamps, and device identifiers.</li>
            <li><strong>Security data</strong> — login information, IP addresses, and access logs for authentication and system safety.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>Your information is used solely to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Authenticate and manage user access securely.</li>
            <li>Enable container tracking and event notifications.</li>
            <li>Maintain system stability and improve reliability.</li>
            <li>Respond to inquiries or service-related requests.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Protection & Security</h2>
        <p>
            We use secure cloud infrastructure, HTTPS/TLS 1.3 encryption, and role-based access control to prevent unauthorized access.
            Authentication is managed using encrypted JWT tokens, and sensitive data is stored securely in our SQL Server database.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
            C.A.T.S. does not share or sell your data for marketing. Information may only be shared with trusted partners (such as
            hosting or SMS gateway providers) bound by confidentiality, or when required by law.
        </p>


        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
            In line with POPIA, you may request to access, update, or delete your data at any time.
            You can also withdraw consent to data processing or lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator of South Africa.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
            The TrackIT website uses only essential cookies for login and authentication purposes.
            We do not use analytics or advertising cookies.
        </p>
        

    
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how your data is handled, please contact us:</p>
            <h3>C.A.T.S. Container Asset Tracking Services</h3>
            <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> 49 Warberson Avenue, Bluff 4052, KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa</p>
            <p><i class="fas fa-phone"></i> +27 (31) 466 2608 | +27 (31) 466 4077</p>
            <p><i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> info@cats.africa</p>
 
    </div>

    <footer class="footer">
        <p>&copy; 2025 TrackIT. All rights reserved. <a href="/Home/Index">Home</a></p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
